Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: THE EXEMPT ORGANIZATION HAS CHANGED ITS ACCOUNTING YEAR FROM A CALENDAR YEAR BASIS TO A FISCAL YEAR BASIS USING JUNE AS THE TAX YEAR-END. AS A RESULT, A SHORT-PERIOD RETURN WAS REQUIRED FOR THE SIX MONTHS ENDED 06/30/15. AS A RESULT, THE TAX YEARS SHOWN ON SCHEDULE A, PART II ARE INCORRECT. COLUMN BY COLUMN, THE PERIODS SHOWN ARE AS FOLLOWS: COLUMN TAX YEAR END (A) 12/31/2014 (B) 06/30/2015 (C) 06/30/2016 (D) 06/30/2017 (E) 06/30/2018 ALL TAX PERIODS, OTHER THAN THE SIX MONTHS ENDED 06/30/2015, ARE 12 MONTHS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CORCORAN AND JOHNSON PROVIDE ADVOCACY SERVICES TO FEEDING TAMPA BAY. THEY ARE ENGAGED VIA A MONTHLY RETAINER. SERVICES PROVIDED INCLUDE CREATING ADVOCACY AND AWARENESS OF THE CAUSE OF FOOD INSECURITY AND DEVELOPING OPPORTUNITIES TO MEET AND DISCUSS PROGRAMS AND SERVICES WITH ELECTED OFFICIALS AND OTHER OPINION LEADERS AND DECISION MAKERS.
THE ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE TO BE USED ONLY FOR DIRECT SERVICE DELIVERY ACTIVITIES, SUCH AS DIRECT DISTRIBUTION OF FOOD TO AGENCIES OR TO NEEDY INDIVIDUALS.
